This website uses a GitHub/Vale/Hugo/Netlify publishing pipeline. I write the content in Visual Studio Code, with Markdown extensions and Vale rules [I designed](https://github.com/dfinr/www.dfinr.com/tree/master/.vale/dfinr), plus others I adapted from [GitLab](https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md), [Google](https://developers.google.com/terms/site-policies), [proselint](https://github.com/errata-ai/proselint/blob/master/LICENSE), [Microsoft](https://github.com/MicrosoftDocs/microsoft-style-guide/), and [write-good](https://github.com/errata-ai/write-good/blob/master/LICENSE).

---

I run Hugo locally to preview the draft content. Once I'm happy with a revision, I [push that to GitHub](https://github.com/dfinr/www.dfinr.com), where a Netlify action builds and publishes the site. 

Vale also has a GitHub Action to lint Markdown files before publishing, which is useful in a multi-user environment. I'm the only author on this site so I've disabled it to improve deployment time. 

Vale provides real-time spellcheck with a custom vocabulary and style guide hints like Grammarly and other commercial tools, but with full control over the style rules. Please sponsor this project on [opencollective.com/vale](https://opencollective.com/vale).
